**To allocate a Dedicated Host**

The following ``allocate-hosts`` example allocates a single Dedicated Host in the specified Availability Zone. ::

    aws ec2 allocate-hosts \
        --instance-type m5.large \
        --availability-zone us-east-1a \
        --quantity 1

Output::

    {
        "HostIds": [
            "h-0abcdef1234567890"
        ]
    }
